# Fast gate on the content actually being committed. lint-staged stashes
# unstaged work and runs against the staged blobs, so `git add` of a badly
# formatted file followed by `npm run format` (which only fixes the working
# tree) still fails here — a whole-repo `prettier --check` would not catch it.
# Typecheck follows on the whole project, because types are not per-file.
# The `&&` matters: without it a lint-staged failure would be masked by a
# passing typecheck, since the hook's exit status is that of its last command.
npx --no -- lint-staged && npm run typecheck
